hor)|Charlotte Gray]]\n| 1948\n|\n| novelist, non-fiction\n| ''[[Mrs. King]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[R. W. Gray]]\n|\n| \n| short stories\n| ''Crisp'', ''Entropic''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ethel Grayson]]\n| 1890\n| 1980\n| novelist, poet\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Nick Green (writer)|Nick Green]]\n| \n| \n| playwright\n| ''Body Politic''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Robert Joseph Greene]]\n| 1973\n|\n| children's literature, romantic fiction\n| ''This High School Has Closets'', ''The Gay Icon Classics of the World''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ed Greenwood]]\n| 1959\n|\n| fantasy\n| ''[[Forgotten Realms]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Darren Greer]]\n| 1968\n| \n| novelist\n| ''[[Still Life with June]]'', ''Just Beneath My Skin ''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Doris Gregory]]\n| \n| \n| autobiographer\n| ''How I Won the War For the Allies: One Sassy Canadian Soldier's Story''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Daniel Grenier]]\n| 1980\n|\n| novelist, short stories\n| ''L\u2019ann\u00e9e la plus longue''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Taras Grescoe]]\n|\n| \n| creative non-fiction\n| ''[[Sacr\u00e9 Blues]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Grey Owl]]\n| 1888\n| 1938\n| conservationist\n| ''Grey Owl and the Beaver'', ''City of the Ancients''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Claude-Henri Grignon]]\n| 1894\n| 1976\n| novelist, satirist\n| ''Un Homme et son p\u00e9ch\u00e9''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Lionel Groulx]]\n| 1878\n| 1967\n| historian\n| ''[[The Call of the Race]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Frederick Phillip Grove]]\n| 1879\n| 1948\n| novelist\n| ''Settlers of the Marsh'', ''Consider Her Ways''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Brett Josef Grubisic]]\n|\n| \n| novelist, critic\n| ''The Age of Cities''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Katia Grubisic]]\n| 1978\n| \n| poet, short stories\n| ''what if red ran out''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Agn\u00e8s Gruda]]\n| \n| \n| journalist, short story writer\n| ''Onze petites trahisons''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Christian Guay-Poliquin]]\n| 1982\n| \n| novelist\n| ''Le fil des ki