es'' (2006)\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Alexander Knox]]\n| 1907\n| 1995\n| actor, novelist\n|''Night Of The White Bear''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Tamai Kobayashi]]\n| 1965\n|\n| short stories, novelist\n| ''Prairie Ostrich''\n|-\n|scope=\"row\" | [[Eric Koch]]\n| 1919\n|\n| novelist\n|''Premonitions: A novel'' \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Joy Kogawa]]\n| 1935\n|\n| poet, novelist\n| ''Obasan'', ''Itsuka''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Miodrag Kojadinovi\u0107]]\n| 1961\n|\n| short story writer, poet\n| ''\u00c9rotiques Supr\u00e8mes'', ''Under Thunderous Skies''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sergio Kokis]]\n| 1944\n|\n| novelist, poet, short stories\n| ''Le Pavillon des miroirs'', ''Les amants d'Alfama'', ''Culs-de-sac''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Gordon Korman]]\n| 1963\n| \n| \n|''Why Did the Underwear Cross the Road'' \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Myrna Kostash]]\n| 1944\n| \n| \n|''Bloodlines: A Journey into Eastern Europe''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Shane Koyczan]]\n| 1976\n| \n| \n|''Our Deathbeds will be Thirsty (2012, House of Parlance Media)''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Greg Kramer]]\n| 1961\n| 2013\n| novelist, playwright\n| ''The Pursemonger of fugu'', ''Couchwarmer'', ''Wally''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Philip Kreiner]]\n| 1950\n|\n| novelist, short stories\n| ''People Like Us in a Place Like This''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Henry Kreisel]]\n| 1922\n| 1991\n| novelist\n| ''The Rich Man''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[John Krizanc]]\n| 1956\n|\n| playwright\n| ''[[Tamara (play)|Tamara]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Robert Kroetsch]]\n| 1927\n| 2011\n| novelist, poet\n| ''The Studhorse Man'', ''The Hornbooks of Rita K''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Kathryn Kuitenbrouwer]]\n| 1965\n|\n| novelist, short stories\n| ''Way Up'', ''The Nettle Spinner'', ''All the Broken Things''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Janice Kulyk Keefer]]\n| 1952\n|\n| novelist, poet\n| ''Constellations'', ''The Green Library''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[J. D. Kurtness]]\n| \n|\n| fiction\n| ''De vengeance''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" |