lan]]\n| 1905\n| 1979\n| History, biography\n| ''The Ardent Exile: The Life and Times of Thos. Darcy McGee''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Wendy Phillips (author)|Wendy Phillips]]\n|\n| \n| children's literature\n| ''Fishtailing''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Lorne Pierce]]\n| 1890\n| 1961\n| literary critic\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Joseph Jomo Pierre]]\n|\n| \n| playwright\n| ''Shakespeare's Nigga''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sarah Pinder]]\n|\n| \n| poet\n| ''Cutting Room'', ''Common Place''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Joseph Pivato]]\n| 1946\n|\n| literary critic, editor\n| ''Echo: Essays on Other Literature'', ''Contrasts: Comparative Essays on Italian-Canadian Writing''.\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Michel Pleau]]\n| 1964\n|\n| poet\n| ''La lenteur du monde'', ''La travers\u00e9e de la nuit''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Casey Plett]]\n|\n| \n| short stories\n| ''A Safe Girl to Love''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Craig Poile]]\n|\n| \n| poet\n| ''First Crack'', ''True Concessions''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Daniel Poliquin]]\n| 1953\n| \n| \n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sharon Pollock]]\n| 1936\n|\n| \n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Michael Poole (producer)|Michael Poole]]\n|\n| \n| non-fiction\n| ''[[Romancing Mary Jane]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Liza Potvin]]\n| 1958\n|\n| non-fiction\n| ''[[White Lies (for my mother)]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jacques Poulin]]\n| 1937\n|\n| novelist\n| ''[[Volkswagen Blues]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Christine Pountney]]\n| 1971\n|\n| novelist\n| ''Last Chance Texaco''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jo\u00ebl Pourbaix]]\n| 1958\n|\n| poet\n| ''Le mal du pays est un art oubli\u00e9''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[B.W. Powe]]\n| 1955\n| \n| philosopher\n| ''A Canada of Light''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Kerry Lee Powell]]\n|\n| \n| poet, short stories\n| ''The Inheritance'', ''Willem de Kooning's Paintbrush''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Craig Francis Power]]\n|\n| \n| novelist\n| ''Blood Relatives'', ''The Hope'', ''Skeet Love''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[E. J. Pratt]]\n| 1883\n| 1964\n| poet\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Steven Price (writer)|Steven Price]]\n| \n|\n| poet, novelist\n| ''Anatomy of Keys'', ''Into That Darkness''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Robert Priest]]\n| 1951\n| \n| poet\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Kate Pullinger]]\n|\n| \n| novels, experimental/online fiction\n| ''The Mistress of Nothing''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Al Purdy]]\n| 1918\n| 2000\n| poet\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Andrew Pyper]]\n| 1968\n|\n| novelist\n| ''Lost Girls'', ''The Trade Mission''\n|}\n\n==Q==\n<!-- NOTE: Writers are only to be listed here if they already have a Wikipedia article. Dead links and offsite links will be removed. -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; line-height:18px; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15%;\"| Name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5%;\"| Born\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5%;\"| Died\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Genre\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:45%;\"| Notable works\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Rachel Qitsualik-Tinsley]]\n| \n| \n| young adult literature\n| ''Skraelings'', ''How Things Came to Be''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sean Qitsualik-Tinsley]]\n| \n| \n| young adult literature\n| ''Skraelings'', ''How Things Came to Be''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Darlene Quaife]]\n| 1948\n| \n| novelist\n| ''Bone Bird''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Andy Quan]]\n| 1969\n| \n| novelist\n| ''Calendar Boy'', ''Slant'', ''Six Positions''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Paul Quarrington]]\n| 1953\n| 2009\n| novelist, screenwriter\n| ''[[Whale Music]]'', ''[[King Leary]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Meredith Quartermain]]\n| 1950\n| \n| poet, fiction\n| ''Vancouver Walking'', ''Recipes from the Red Planet''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sina Queyras]]\n| 1963\n| \n| poet, novelist\n| ''Lemon Hound'', ''MxT'', ''Autobiography of Childhood''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Pascale Quiviger]]\n| 1969\n| \n| novelist\n| ''Le Cercle parfait''\n|}\n\n==R==\n<!-- NOTE: Writers are only to be listed here if they