vania''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Tom Walmsley]]\n| 1948\n|\n| novelist, dramatist, poet\n| ''Doctor Tin''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Eric Walters]]\n| 1957\n|\n| novelist\n| ''Safe As Houses'', ''Shattered'', ''Camp X'', ''Run''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[John Leigh Walters]]\n| 1933\n| \n| creative non-fiction\n| ''[[A Very Capable Life]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Russell Wangersky]]\n|\n| \n| novelist, short stories, journalist\n| ''The Hour of Bad Decisions'', ''[[Burning Down the House: Fighting Fires and Losing Myself|Burning Down the House]]'', ''The Glass Harmonica''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ryan Ward (actor)|Ryan Ward]]\n|\n| \n| screenwriter\n| ''[[Son of the Sunshine]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sabrina Ward Harrison]]\n| 1975\n|\n| spirituality, self-help\n| ''Spilling Open''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Dianne Warren]]\n| 1950\n|\n| playwright, novelist, short stories\n| ''Serpent in the Night Sky'', ''Club Chernobyl'', ''Cool Water''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[David Watmough]]\n| 1926\n|\n| playwright, novelist, short stories\n| ''Names for the Numbered Years'', ''The Time of Kingfishers''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sheila Watson (writer)|Sheila Watson]]\n| 1909\n| 1998\n| novelist\n| ''The Double Hook''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Alison Watt (writer)|Alison Watt]]\n| 1957\n|\n| creative non-fiction, poet\n| ''[[The Last Island]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Thomas Waugh]]\n| 1948\n|\n| academic, art and film historian\n| ''Out/Lines: Underground Gay Graphics From Before Stonewall'', ''Lust Unearthed: Vintage Gay Graphics from the DuBek Collection''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Alison Wearing]]\n| 1967\n|\n| travel\n| ''Honeymoon in Purdah''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jessica L. Webb]]\n|\n| \n| mysteries\n| ''Pathogen'', ''Repercussions''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Barry Webster (writer)|Barry Webster]]\n| 1961\n|\n| novels, short stories; [[magic realism]]\n| ''The Sound of All Flesh'', ''The Lava in My Bones''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Andrew Wedderburn]]\n| \n| \n| novelis