ittall]]\n| 1976\n| \n| \n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Rudy Wiebe]]\n| 1934\n|\n| novelist\n| ''A Discovery of Strangers'', ''The Temptations of Big Bear''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Helen Waldstein Wilkes]]\n|\n| \n| creative non-fiction\n| ''[[Letters from the Lost]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Fred Williams (journalist)|Fred Williams]]\n| 1863\n| 1944\n| journalism, history\n| ''The Canadian Book of Days''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jeffery Williams]]\n| 1920\n| 2011\n| military historian\n| ''Byng of Vimy'', ''Far from Home''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Deborah Willis (author)|Deborah Willis]]\n| 1982\n|\n| fiction writer\n| ''Vanishing'', ''The Dark and Other Love Stories''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jenny Heijun Wills]]\n|\n|\n| memoirist\n| ''Older Sister, Not Necessarily Related''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Alan R. Wilson]]\n|\n|\n| novels, poetry\n| ''Before the Flood''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Douglas Wilson (activist)|Douglas Wilson]]\n| 1950\n| 1992\n| novelist, poet\n| ''Labour of Love''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Eric Wilson (author)|Eric Wilson]]\n| 1940\n|\n| mysteries\n| ''Tom Austen Series'' (9 books),  ''Liz Austen Series'' (6 books), ''Tom and Liz Austen Series'' (5 books)\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ethel Wilson]]\n| 1888\n| 1980\n| novelist\n| ''Swamp Angel'', ''[[Hetty Dorval]]'', ''The Window''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[John Wilson (Canadian young adults' writer)|John Wilson]]\n| 1951\n|\n| historical fiction\n| ''[[Four Steps to Death]]'', ''Flames of the Tiger'', ''And in the Morning''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jonathan Wilson (actor)|Jonathan Wilson]]\n| \n|\n| playwright\n| ''My Own Private Oshawa'', ''Kilt''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Robert Charles Wilson]]\n| 1953\n|\n| science fiction\n| ''Julian Comstock, A Story of 22nd. America'', ''Darwinia'', ''Axis'', ''Spin''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sheri-D Wilson]]\n|\n| \n| poet, playwright\n| ''The Sweet Taste of Lightning'', ''Boy Wonder''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jia Qing Wilson-Yang]]\n|\n| \n| novelist\n| ''