ty Words for Sorrow]]'', ''Blackfly Season''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ali Blythe]]\n| \n| \n| poet\n| ''Twoism''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Adam Bock]]\n| \n| \n| playwright\n| ''The Receptionist'', ''The Drunken City''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Dennis Bock]]\n| 1964\n| \n| novelist, short stories\n| ''[[The Ash Garden]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Maxime Raymond Bock]]\n| 1981\n| \n| novelist, short stories\n| ''Atavismes'', ''Les noyades secondaires''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Michel Bock]]\n| 1971\n| \n| historian, non-fiction\n| ''Quand la nation d\u00e9bordait les fronti\u00e8res''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Fred Bodsworth]]\n| 1918\n| 2012\n| journalist, naturalist\n| ''[[The Last of the Curlews]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Christian B\u00f6k]]\n| 1966\n| \n| poet\n| ''[[Eunoia (book)|Eunoia]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Stephanie Bolster]]\n| 1969\n| \n| poet\n| ''White Stone: The Alice Poems''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Carol Bolt]]\n| 1941\n| 2000\n| playwright\n| ''Buffalo Jump'', ''One Night Stand'', ''Red Emma, Queen of the Anarchists''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Kenneth Bonert]]\n| \n| \n| novelist, short stories\n| ''The Lion Seeker''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Shane Book]]\n| \n| \n| poet\n| ''Ceiling of Sticks'', ''Congotronic''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Walter Borden]]\n| 1942\n| \n| playwright, poet\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Kathryn Borel]]\n| 1979\n| \n| memoirist\n| ''Corked''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Roo Borson]]\n| 1952\n| \n| poet\n| ''Short Journey Upriver Toward Oishida''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Monique Bosco]]\n| 1927\n| 2007\n| journalist, novelist, poet, short stories\n| ''La femme de Loth''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[G\u00e9rard Bouchard]]\n| 1943\n| \n| non-fiction, novelist\n| ''Gen\u00e8se des nations et cultures du Nouveau Monde''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Michel Marc Bouchard]]\n| 1958\n| \n| playwright\n| ''[[Lilies (play)|Lilies]]'', ''The Orphan Muses''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Paul Bouchard]]\n| 1908\n| 1997\n| journalist\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"r