s]]\n| \n|\n| poet\n| ''That Other Beauty'', ''Cloud Physics''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Steven Erikson]]\n| 1959\n|\n| novelist\n| ''Malazan Book of the Fallen series''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ann Eriksson]]\n| 1956\n|\n| novelist\n| ''In the Hands of Anubis''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Gloria Escomel]]\n| 1941\n|\n| novelist, dramatist, journalist\n| ''Pi\u00e8ges'', ''Fruit de la passion''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Michael Estok]]\n| 1939\n| 1989\n| poet\n| ''A Plague Year Journal''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Hubert Evans (author)|Hubert Evans]]\n| 1892\n| 1986\n| novelist, poet, short stories, journalism, young adult literature\n| ''Mist on the River''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jon Evans (author)|Jon Evans]]\n| 1973\n|\n| novelist\n| ''Dark Places''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Stanley Evans (author)|Stanley Evans]]\n| \n|\n| novelist\n| ''Seaweed'' series of crime fiction\n|}\n\n==F==\n<!-- NOTE: Writers are only to be listed here if they already have a Wikipedia article. Dead links and offsite links will be removed. -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; line-height:18px; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15%;\"| Name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5%;\"| Born\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5%;\"| Died\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Genre\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:45%;\"| Notable works\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Emil Fackenheim]]\n| 1916\n| 2003\n| historian, philosopher\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Terry Fallis]]\n| \n|\n| humorist\n| ''The Best Laid Plans''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Alain Farah]]\n| 1979\n|\n| novelist, poet\n| ''Matamore no 29'', ''Pourquoi Boulogne''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Edmundo Farolan]]\n| 1943\n| \n| poet, playwright, novelist\n| ''Itinerancias'', ''Hexalogia Teatral'', ''Love, Travels and Other Memoirs of a Filipino Writer''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Brian Fawcett]]\n| 1944\n|\n| novelist, non-fiction\n| ''Virtual Clearcut: Or, the Way Things Are in My Hometown'', ''[[Cambodia: A Book for People