unn]]\n| 1949\n|\n| novelist, poet\n| ''Tracing Iris'', ''Faceless''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Kristjana Gunnars]]\n| 1948\n|\n| poet, novelist\n| ''Settlement Poems'', ''One-Eyed Moon Maps''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[David Gurr]]\n| 1936\n|\n| novelist, playwright\n| ''The Ring Master''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ralph Gustafson]]\n| 1909\n| 1995\n| poet\n| ''Fire on Stone''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Don Gutteridge (writer)|Don Gutteridge]]\n| 1937\n|\n| poet, novelist\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Guy Lawson]]\n| 1963\n| \n| journalist\n| ''[[War Dogs (2016 film)|War Dogs]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sandra Gwyn]]\n| 1935\n| 2000\n| journalist\n| ''The Private Capital: Ambition and Love in the Age of Macdonald and Laurier''\n|}\n\n==H==\n<!-- NOTE: Writers are only to be listed here if they already have a Wikipedia article. Dead links and offsite links will be removed. -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; line-height:18px; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15%;\"| Name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5%;\"| Born\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5%;\"| Died\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Genre\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:45%;\"| Notable works\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Samra Habib]]\n|\n| \n| photographer, memoirist\n| ''We Have Always Been Here''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Rawi Hage]]\n| 1964\n|\n| novelist\n| ''[[De Niro's Game]]'', ''Cockroach'', ''Carnival''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Joan Haggerty]]\n|\n| \n| \n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Roderick Haig-Brown]]\n| 1941\n|\n| \n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Arthur Hailey]]\n| 1920\n| 2004\n| novelist\n| ''Hotel'', ''Airport''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Thomas Chandler Haliburton]]\n| \n|\n| \n| ''The Clockmaker''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Louis Hamelin]]\n| 1959\n|\n| novelist, short stories, literary critic\n| ''La Rage'', ''Sauvages'', ''La Constellation du Lynx''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ian Hamilton (writer)|Ian Hamilton]]\n|\n| \n| journalist, mysteries\n| ''The Water Rat of W