e at the End of the Day]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[\u00c9mile Martel (writer)|\u00c9mile Martel]]\n| 1941\n|\n| poet, short stories\n| ''Pour orchestre et po\u00e8te seul''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Yann Martel]]\n| 1963\n|\n| novelist, short stories\n| ''[[Life of Pi]]'', ''The High Mountains of Portugal''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Camille Martin]]\n| 1956\n|\n| poet, collage artist\n| ''Sonnets'', ''Looms''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Claire Martin (writer)|Claire Martin]]\n| 1914\n| 2014\n| \n| ''La joue droite''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Paul Nicholas Mason]]\n| 1958\n|\n| novelist, playwright\n| ''Battered Soles'', ''The Red Dress'', ''The Night Drummer''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Vincent Massey]]\n| 1887\n| 1967\n| historian\n| ''On being Canadian'', ''Speaking of Canada'', ''Confederation on the march''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Elan Mastai]]\n|\n|\n| screenwriter, novelist\n| ''[[The F Word (2013 film)|The F Word]]'', ''All Our Wrong Todays''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Carol Matas]]\n| 1949\n|\n| novelist\n| ''After the War'', ''Daniel's Story''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Shirlee Smith Matheson]]\n| 1943\n| \n| \n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[John Bentley Mays]]\n| 1941\n| 2016\n| journalist, novelist, memoirist\n| ''In the Jaws of the Black Dogs'', ''Power in the Blood''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Susan Mayse]]\n| 1948\n|\n| creative non-fiction\n| ''Awen'', ''[[Ginger: The Life and Death of Albert Goodwin|Ginger]]'', ''Merlin's Web''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Julie Mazzieri]]\n| 1975\n|\n| novelist\n| ''Le discours sur la tombe de l'idiot'', ''La Bosco''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Tawiah M'carthy]]\n|\n| \n| playwright\n| ''Obaaberima''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Colin McAdam (novelist)|Colin McAdam]]\n|\n| \n| novelist\n| ''Some Great Thing'', ''A Beautiful Truth''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Steve McCaffery]]\n| 1947\n| \n| \n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Julia McCarthy]]\n| \n| \n| poet\n| ''Return from Erebus'', ''All the Names Between''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Nellie McClung]]\n| 1873\n| 1951\n| journalist\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Kathleen McConnell]] (a/k/a Kathy Mac)\n| \n|\n| poet, academic\n| ''Nail Builders Plan for Strength and Growth'', ''The Hundefraulein Papers''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Derek McCormack (writer)|Derek McCormack]]\n| 1969\n|\n| novelist, short stories\n| ''Dark Rides'', ''The Haunted Hillbilly''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Eric McCormack (writer)|Eric McCormack]]\n| 1938\n|\n| novelist\n| ''The Paradise Motel'', ''First Blast of the Trumpet Against the Monstrous Regiment of Women''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Edward McCourt]]\n| 1907\n| 1972\n| novelist, non-fiction\n| ''Music at the Close''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[John McCrae]]\n| 1872\n| 1918\n| poet\n| \"[[In Flanders' Fields]]\"\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Kathleen McCracken]]\n| 1960\n| \n| poet\n| ''Blue Light, Bay and College''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Derek McCulloch (comics)|Derek McCulloch]]\n| 1964\n|\n| graphic novelist, children's literature\n| ''[[Stagger Lee (comics)|Stagger Lee]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Thomas McCulloch]]\n| 1776\n| 1843\n| humourist\n| ''The Stepsure Letters''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Colin McDougall]]\n| 1917\n| 1984\n| novelist\n| ''[[Execution (novel)|Execution]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Franklin D. McDowell]]\n| 1888\n| 1965\n| novelist\n| ''The Champlain Road''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jaimie McEvoy]]\n| 1965\n|\n| historian\n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[David McFadden (poet)|David McFadden]]\n| 1940\n| 2018\n| poet, novelist, short story writer\n| ''The Art of Darkness'', ''What's the Score?''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Donna McFarlane (writer)|Donna McFarlane]]\n| 1958\n|\n| novelist\n| ''Division of Surgery''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Leslie McFarlane]] (a/k/a [[Franklin W. Dixon]])\n| 1902\n| 1977\n| children's literature\n| ''[[The Hardy Boys]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sheryl McFarlane]]\n| 1954\n|\n| children's literature, young adult fiction\n| ''Waiting for the Whales'', ''Jessie's Island'', ''Eagle Dreams'', ''Thi