ila Uppal]]\n| 1974\n|\n| poet, novelist\n| ''The Divine Economy of Salvation''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jane Urquhart]]\n| 1949\n|\n| novelist\n| ''Away'', ''[[The Stone Carvers]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Geoffrey Ursell]]\n| 1943\n|\n| novelist, playwright, poet\n| ''Perdue, or How the West Was Lost'', ''Saskatoon Pie''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[David UU (David W. Harris)]]\n| 1948\n| 1994\n| visual poet\n| ''Chopped Liver''\n|}\n\n==V==\n<!-- NOTE: Writers are only to be listed here if they already have a Wikipedia article. Dead links and offsite links will be removed. -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:left; line-height:18px; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15%;\"| Name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5%;\"| Born\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:5%;\"| Died\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\"| Genre\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:45%;\"| Notable works\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[W. D. Valgardson]]\n| 1939\n|\n| novelist, poet, short stories\n| ''The Girl with the Botticelli Face'', ''[[Bloodflowers: Ten Stories]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Pierre Valli\u00e8res]]\n| 1938\n| 1998\n| political essayist\n| ''[[White Niggers of America|Les N\u00e8gres blancs d'Am\u00e9rique]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Edo Van Belkom]]\n| 1962\n|\n| horror\n| ''Army of the Dead'', ''Wyrm Wolf''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Richard Van Camp]]\n| 1971\n|\n| novelist, short stories, children's literature\n| ''[[The Lesser Blessed]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Guy Vanderhaeghe]]\n| 1951\n|\n| novelist, short stories\n| ''[[The Englishman's Boy]]'', ''[[The Last Crossing]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Aritha Van Herk]]\n| 1954\n|\n| novelist\n| ''Judith'', ''No Fixed Address''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[A. E. van Vogt]]\n| 1912\n| 2000\n| science fiction\n| ''[[Children of Tomorrow]]'', ''[[Empire of the Atom]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jean Vanier]]\n| 1928\n|\n| theologian\n| ''Becoming Human''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[M. G. Vassanji]]\n| 1950\n|\n| novelist\