ell Wangersky]]\n|\n| \n| novelist, short stories, journalist\n| ''The Hour of Bad Decisions'', ''[[Burning Down the House: Fighting Fires and Losing Myself|Burning Down the House]]'', ''The Glass Harmonica''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ryan Ward (actor)|Ryan Ward]]\n|\n| \n| screenwriter\n| ''[[Son of the Sunshine]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sabrina Ward Harrison]]\n| 1975\n|\n| spirituality, self-help\n| ''Spilling Open''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Dianne Warren]]\n| 1950\n|\n| playwright, novelist, short stories\n| ''Serpent in the Night Sky'', ''Club Chernobyl'', ''Cool Water''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[David Watmough]]\n| 1926\n|\n| playwright, novelist, short stories\n| ''Names for the Numbered Years'', ''The Time of Kingfishers''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sheila Watson (writer)|Sheila Watson]]\n| 1909\n| 1998\n| novelist\n| ''The Double Hook''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Alison Watt (writer)|Alison Watt]]\n| 1957\n|\n| creative non-fiction, poet\n| ''[[The Last Island]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Thomas Waugh]]\n| 1948\n|\n| academic, art and film historian\n| ''Out/Lines: Underground Gay Graphics From Before Stonewall'', ''Lust Unearthed: Vintage Gay Graphics from the DuBek Collection''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Alison Wearing]]\n| 1967\n|\n| travel\n| ''Honeymoon in Purdah''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jessica L. Webb]]\n|\n| \n| mysteries\n| ''Pathogen'', ''Repercussions''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Barry Webster (writer)|Barry Webster]]\n| 1961\n|\n| novels, short stories; [[magic realism]]\n| ''The Sound of All Flesh'', ''The Lava in My Bones''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Andrew Wedderburn]]\n| \n| \n| novelist\n| ''The Milk Chicken Bomb''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[John Weier]]\n| 1949\n|\n| poet\n| ''Stand the Sacred Tree''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Steve Weiner]]\n|\n| \n| novelist\n| ''The Museum of Love''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[William Weintraub]]\n| 1926\n| \n| \n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Helen Weinzweig]]\n| 1915\n| 2010\n| novelist, short stories\n| ''Basic Black with Pearls'', ''A View from the Roof''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Merrily Weisbord]]\n| \n|\n| journalist\n| ''The Love Queen of Malabar'', ''[[The Valour and the Horror]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Elizabeth Wellburn]]\n|\n| \n| children's literature\n| ''Echoes From the Square''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Zachariah Wells]]\n| 1976\n|\n| poet, critic\n| ''Fool's Errand'', ''Unsettled''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Andrew Westoll]]\n|\n| \n| science, travel, non-fiction\n| ''[[The Chimps of Fauna Sanctuary]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Robert Paul Weston]]\n| 1975\n|\n| poet, children's literature\n| ''Zorgamazoo'', ''Dust City''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Michael Wex]]\n| 1954\n|\n| novelist, playwright, non-fiction\n| ''The Adventures of Micah Mushmelon, Boy Talmudist''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ron Weyman]]\n| 1915\n| 2007\n| television, mystery, memoir\n| ''Sherlock Holmes and the Mark of the Beast'', ''Sherlock Holmes and the Ultimate Disguise'', ''Sherlock Holmes Travels in the Canadian West''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Dawud Wharnsby]]\n| 1972\n|\n| poet, songwriter\n| ''Nasheed Artist''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Thomas Wharton (author)|Thomas Wharton]]\n| 1963\n|\n| novelist\n| ''Salamander'', ''Icefields''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sherry White]]\n|\n| \n| screenwriter\n| ''[[Crackie]]'', ''[[Down to the Dirt]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Joshua Whitehead]]\n|\n| \n| poet, novelist\n| ''Full-Metal Indigiqueer'', ''Johnny Appleseed''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[William Whitehead (Canadian writer)|William Whitehead]]\n| 1931\n| 2018\n| documentarian, memoirist\n| ''Words to Live By''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Zoe Whittall]]\n| 1976\n| \n| \n| \n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Rudy Wiebe]]\n| 1934\n|\n| novelist\n| ''A Discovery of Strangers'', ''The Temptations of Big Bear''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Helen Waldstein Wilkes]]\n|\n| \n| creative non-fiction\n| ''[[Letters from the Lost]]''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Fred Williams (journalist)|Fred Williams]]\n| 1863\n| 1944\n| journalism, history\n| ''The Canadian Book of Days''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jeffery Williams]]\n| 1920\n| 2011\n| military historian\n| ''Byng of Vimy'', ''Far from Home''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Deborah Willis (author)|Deborah Willis]]\n| 1982\n|\n| fiction writer\n| ''Vanishing'', ''The Dark and Other Love Stories''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jenny Heijun Wills]]\n|\n|\n| memoirist\n| ''Older Sister, Not Necessarily Related''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Alan R. Wilson]]\n|\n|\n| novels, poetry\n| ''Before the Flood''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Douglas Wilson (activist)|Douglas Wilson]]\n| 1950\n| 1992\n| novelist, poet\n| ''Labour of Love''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Eric Wilson (author)|Eric Wilson]]\n| 1940\n|\n| mysteries\n| ''Tom Austen Series'' (9 books),  ''Liz Austen Series'' (6 books), ''Tom and Liz Austen Series'' (5 books)\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Ethel Wilson]]\n| 1888\n| 1980\n| novelist\n| ''Swamp Angel'', ''[[Hetty Dorval]]'', ''The Window''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[John Wilson (Canadian young adults' writer)|John Wilson]]\n| 1951\n|\n| historical fiction\n| ''[[Four Steps to Death]]'', ''Flames of the Tiger'', ''And in the Morning''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jonathan Wilson (actor)|Jonathan Wilson]]\n| \n|\n| playwright\n| ''My Own Private Oshawa'', ''Kilt''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Robert Charles Wilson]]\n| 1953\n|\n| science fiction\n| ''Julian Comstock, A Story of 22nd. America'', ''Darwinia'', ''Axis'', ''Spin''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Sheri-D Wilson]]\n|\n| \n| poet, playwright\n| ''The Sweet Taste of Lightning'', ''Boy Wonder''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Jia Qing Wilson-Yang]]\n|\n| \n| novelist\n| ''Small Beauty''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Carol Windley]]\n| 1947\n|\n| novelist, short stories\n| ''Home Schooling''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Rob Winger]]\n| 1974\n| \n| poet\n| ''Muybridge's Horse''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Kathleen Winter]]\n| 1960\n| \n| novelist, short stories\n| ''Boys'', ''Annabel''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Michael Winter (writer)|Michael Winter