ators football|Florida]] in [[Jacksonville, Florida]].<ref name=\"UG16\">{{cite press release|url=http://www.georgiadogs.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/102915aad.html|title=Bulldogs' 2016 Football Schedule Announced|publisher=University of Georgia Department of Athletics|date=October 29, 2015|accessdate=November 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe Bulldogs had hosted three of their four non\u2013conference games, which were against [[Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets football|Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets]] and the [[North Carolina Tar Heels football|North Carolina Tar Heels]] both from the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]], [[Louisiana\u2013Lafayette Ragin' Cajuns football|Louisiana\u2013Lafayette Ragin' Cajuns]] from the [[Sun Belt Conference]], and [[Nicholls State Colonels football|Nicholls State Colonels]] from the [[Southland Conference]].<ref>{{cite web |title=2016 Georgia Bulldogs Football Schedule|url=http://www.fbschedules.com/ncaa-16/2016-georgia-bulldogs-football-schedule.php|publisher=FB Schedules|accessdate=November 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 2016\n| poll = [[2016 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings#AP Poll|AP Poll]] released prior to game\n| timezone = Eastern\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 3\n| time = 5:30 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| neutral = y\n| rank = 18\n| opponent = [[2016 North Carolina Tar Heels football team|North Carolina]]\n| opprank = 22\n| gamename = [[Chick-fil-A Kickoff Game]]\n| site_stadium = [[Georgia Dome]]\n| site_cityst = [[Atlanta|Atlanta, GA]]\n| tv = [[ESPN College Football Saturday Primetime|ESPN]]\n| score = 33\u201324\n| attend = 75,405\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 10\n| time = 12:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| rank = 9\n| opponent = [[2016 Nicholls State Colonels football team|Nicholls State]]\n| site_stadium = [[Sanford Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Athens, Georgia|Athens, GA]]\n| tv = [[SEC Network|SECN]]\n| score = 26\u201324\n| attend = 92,746\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date 