ition   = #10 K\n| hometown   = [[China Grove, NC]]\n| highschool = [[South Rowan High School]]\n| feet   = 6\n| inches = 4\n| weight = 230\n| commitdate   = 1/31/16\n| scout stars  = 3\n| rivals stars = 2\n| 247 stars    = 3\n| espn stars   = 3\n}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit End\n| 40 = \n| year = 2016\n| rivals ref title = 2016 Georgia Football Commitment List\n| scout ref title = 2016 Georgia Commits\n| espn ref title = 2016 Players Commitments \u2013 Georgia\n| rivals school = \n| scouts = \n| scout overall = 10\n| rivals overall = 9\n| 247 overall = 7\n| espn overall = 7\n| accessdate = January 31, 2016\n| collapse = collapsible\n}}\n\nNational Signing Day was on February 3, 2016.\n\n==Schedule==\nGeorgia announced its 2016 football schedule on October 29, 2015. The 2016 schedule consists of 6 home, 4 away, and 2 neutral site games in the regular season. The Bulldogs will host SEC foes [[Auburn Tigers football|Auburn]], [[Tennessee Volunteers football|Tennessee]], and [[Vanderbilt Commodores football|Vanderbilt]], and will travel to [[Kentucky Wildcats football|Kentucky]], [[Missouri Tigers football|Missouri]], [[Ole Miss Rebels football|Ole Miss]], and [[South Carolina Gamecocks football|South Carolina]]. Georgia will go against [[Florida Gators football|Florida]] in [[Jacksonville, Florida]].<ref name=\"UG16\">{{cite press release|url=http://www.georgiadogs.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/102915aad.html|title=Bulldogs' 2016 Football Schedule Announced|publisher=University of Georgia Department of Athletics|date=October 29, 2015|accessdate=November 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe Bulldogs had hosted three of their four non\u2013conference games, which were against [[Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets football|Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets]] and the [[North Carolina Tar Heels football|North Carolina Tar Heels]] both from the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]], [[Louisiana\u2013Lafayette Ragin' Cajuns football|Louisiana\u2013Lafayette Ragin' Cajuns]] from the [[Sun Belt Conference]], and [[Nicholls State Colonels football|Nicholls State Colonels]] from the [[Southland Conference]].<ref>{{cite web |title=2016 Georgia Bulldogs Football Schedule|url=http://www.fbschedules.com/ncaa-16/2016-georgia-bulldogs-football-schedule.php|publisher=FB Schedules|accessdate=November 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 2016\n| poll = [[2016 NCAA Division I FBS football rankings#AP Poll|AP Poll]] released prior to game\n| timezone = Eastern\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 3\n| time = 5:30 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| neutral = y\n| rank = 18\n| opponent = [[2016 North Carolina Tar Heels football team|North Carolina]]\n| opprank = 22\n| gamename = [[Chick-fil-A Kickoff Game]]\n| site_stadium = [[Georgia Dome]]\n| site_cityst = [[Atlanta|Atlanta, GA]]\n| tv = [[ESPN College Football Saturday Primetime|ESPN]]\n| score = 33\u201324\n| attend = 75,405\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 10\n| time = 12:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| rank = 9\n| opponent = [[2016 Nicholls State Colonels football team|Nicholls State]]\n| site_stadium = [[Sanford Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Athens, Georgia|Athens, GA]]\n| tv = [[SEC Network|SECN]]\n| score = 26\u201324\n| attend = 92,746\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 17\n| time = 7:30 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| away = y\n| rank = 16\n| opponent = [[2016 Missouri Tigers football team|Missouri]]\n| site_stadium = [[Faurot Field]]\n| site_cityst = [[Columbia, Missouri|Columbia, MO]]\n| tv = SECN\n| score = 28\u201327\n| attend = 57,098\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 24\n| time = 12:00 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| rank = 12\n| opponent = [[2016 Ole Miss Rebels football team|Ole Miss]]\n| opprank = 23\n| site_stadium = [[Vaught\u2013Hemingway Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Oxford, Mississippi|Oxford, MS]]\n| tv = [[ESPN College Football|ESPN]]\n| score = 14\u201345\n| attend = 65,483\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 1\n| time = 3:30 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| rank = 25